name: Test -> Control Module 3,
description: Measure the voltage across the input and output terminals of Control Module 3 to determine where voltage is present. This will help confirm if voltage is reaching both the input and output sides, and whether a voltage drop or discontinuity exists inside or after the module., outcome='Voltage is present at Control Input Cable (+) 3 (11.96 V), but not at Control Output Cable (+) 3 or either negative terminal (all ~0.0064 V). This indicates voltage is reaching the input of Control Module 3 but not passing through to the output side. No polarity inversion detected.\nCurrent persistent circuit state [differences with the starting state]:\nNo circuit-level changes introduced by diagnostics.', precise_action_cost=80.0, cost_breakdown=[('measure_voltage', 20.0), ('measure_voltage', 20.0), ('measure_voltage', 20.0), ('measure_voltage', 20.0)], simplified_outcome=None)] 
